1
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:57,015
YUMI'S CELLS 3

2
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:02,020
EPISODE 10
RUDOLPH

3
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:22,541
Hey, Jang PD.

4
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:25,877
- We just arrived at the hotel.
- Ms. Kim!

5
00:01:25,961 --> 00:01:29,798
Hi, we're at a pub. You should come.

6
00:01:30,132 --> 00:01:32,050
- A pub?
- Yes.

7
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:35,304
It's close to the hotel.

8
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:38,348
Yu-mi? Tell her to hurry up.

9
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:41,268
The Chief Editor says to hurry.

10
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:44,313
- The chicken is here.
- Yes, come with Shin PD.

11
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,982
Okay, I'll ask him.

12
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,238
Let's go, let's go.

13
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:56,033
This is a chance to get closer
to Soon-rok while drinking.

14
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:58,869
Yes! Let's get some chicken!

15
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:01,163
They said there's chicken.

16
00:02:01,413 --> 00:02:03,123
Your room is on the fourth floor.

17
00:02:05,334 --> 00:02:09,379
The Chief Editor is at the pub now
and wants us to come.

18
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:11,715
Would you like to go?
I can take you there.

19
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:16,261
- What about you?
- I have some work to do.

20
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:19,264
If you come down after unpacking,
I'll take you there.

21
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:22,768
Forget it. Why go without Soon-rok?

22
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:26,480
You're not eating the chicken?

23
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:29,733
I'm tired too. I should rest.

24
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:35,280
- Do you want to do that?
- Yes. Please tell them I'm resting.

25
00:02:35,614 --> 00:02:36,615
Sure.

26
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:40,827
You're not eating the chicken?

27
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:43,622
But I want to eat chicken.

28
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:03,183
Fourth floor. Door closing.

29
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:05,644
Where is your...

30
00:03:06,478 --> 00:03:07,479
We're on the same floor.

31
00:03:09,523 --> 00:03:11,525
I'm sharing the room
with the Chief Editor.

32
00:03:11,775 --> 00:03:12,943
Oh, really?

33
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,319
That must be uncomfortable.

34
00:03:15,779 --> 00:03:17,030
Such is the sorrow of a junior employee.

35
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,000
Silence again.

36
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:31,712
Isn't it strange?

37
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,756
The silence that was so unbearable
just a few days ago...

38
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:38,009
Why does it feel so sweet now?

39
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:42,764
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

40
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,110
Well.

41
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,737
Have a good night, Ms. Kim.

42
00:03:57,279 --> 00:03:58,613
Yes, thank you for your hard work.

43
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,277
The sweet silence.

44
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:38,987
Soon-rok smells so good.

45
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,197
I wonder what cologne he uses.

46
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:43,325
Is Soon-rok's hair naturally curly?

47
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:44,659
SWEET SILENCE
IS SOON-ROK'S HAIR NATURALLY CURLY?

48
00:04:44,743 --> 00:04:47,621
Soon-rok, take off your glasses
and wear contacts.

49
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:50,415
But it's Soon-rok's birthday.

50
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:58,590
Soon-rok's birthday isn't over yet.

51
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:13,730
We were together all day on his birthday.

52
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,441
- Should we just let it pass?
- Yeah.

53
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:18,360
We already got him a birthday cake.

54
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:20,403
Come on, that was the one Na-hee bought.

55
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,202
Isn't it too late to send a gift?

56
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:29,704
Wouldn't it be weirder
to just stay quiet and move on?

57
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:31,998
That's true.

58
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,545
Right. Doing nothing is weirder.
It'll seem like I'm still mad.

59
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:40,173
Something that he won't feel
uncomfortable to receive.

60
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:45,387
Like this one.

61
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:50,809
Is this too cheap?

62
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:53,687
Then...

63
00:05:57,732 --> 00:05:58,942
This one's better.

64
00:06:00,652 --> 00:06:02,153
But if a perfume isn't his taste...

65
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,365
he won't wear it, right?

66
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:07,784
This one is a bit much.

67
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:09,953
No, not this one.

68
00:06:10,579 --> 00:06:12,247
But he doesn't drink...

69
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:15,458
at all, or does he?

70
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:18,670
Picking gifts is so hard.

71
00:06:26,428 --> 00:06:28,513
What? There are only ten minutes
of his birthday left?

72
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,390
Let's just send anything.

73
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:33,184
It'll be meaningless to send it
after 12 o'clock.

74
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:34,394
Gosh, what should I send?

75
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:36,646
Right.

76
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:37,939
This one's the best.

77
00:06:38,023 --> 00:06:39,608
It's safe. Let's pick the safe one.

78
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:44,070
SEND TO SHIN SOON-ROK

79
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:51,494
Hold on. What if you're just
waking a sleeping person needlessly?

80
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:55,624
And isn't he sharing a room
with the Chief Editor?

81
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:59,002
What if the Chief Editor sees it
and gets the wrong idea?

82
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:02,172
That's...

83
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,257
That's not right.

84
00:07:16,478 --> 00:07:17,854
The wind feels nice.

85
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:26,905
- It's Soon-rok!
- It's Soon-rok!

86
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,157
Soon-rok is awake.

87
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,034
The Chief Editor isn't with him either.

88
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,786
The timing is perfect!

89
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,204
What time is it?

90
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,581
It's 11:57 p.m.
There are still three minutes left.

91
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:39,167
- Yu-mi, let's send the gift!
- Yu-mi, let's send the gift!

92
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:46,841
I'm sending this
before your birthday is over...

93
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:48,593
Happy birthday.

94
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:52,430
- Press it!
- Press it!

95
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:54,474
Press it!

96
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:13,994
- He's reading it.
- He's reading it.

97
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:25,755
He's writing a reply.

98
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:32,470
Soon-rok is writing a long reply.

99
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,055
No, he's deleting it.

100
00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:36,224
He must be thinking about it.

101
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:46,484
He's writing again.

102
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:05,628
He replied!

103
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,221
What did he say?

104
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:17,057
Thank you.

105
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,266
I'll enjoy the coffee.

106
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:19,934
Have a good night.

107
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,440
He sent a smiley!

108
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:31,321
It's a smiley, everyone. See?

109
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:36,117
That means you like them.

110
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:38,495
- Right?
- Right!

111
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:50,381
That night, a smiley moon
rose over the village.

112
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,342
This is crazy.

113
00:09:58,181 --> 00:09:59,474
I feel good.

114
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:04,187
It's been so long
since I've felt this way.

115
00:10:05,522 --> 00:10:06,523
It feels like my heart

116
00:10:06,898 --> 00:10:08,775
has gone soft.

117
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,316
Chief Editor Ahn.

118
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:54,070
- Oh, Yu-mi.
- You're up early.

119
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:56,072
- Yes, please have a seat.
- Okay.

120
00:10:58,783 --> 00:10:59,784
Ms. Kim.

121
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:01,786
Why didn't you come yesterday?

122
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,664
I was so tired yesterday.

123
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:07,125
I really wanted to go,
but I just couldn't.

124
00:11:07,709 --> 00:11:08,751
That was a good call.

125
00:11:09,544 --> 00:11:11,796
You drank a lot yesterday, right?

126
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,382
No, I've cut back a lot.

127
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:17,177
Ida gives me such a hard time about it.

128
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:21,514
- Ida's scary about that, right?
- Tell me about it.

129
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:25,643
- Would you like some coffee?
- Yes. I'll have an iced Americano too.

130
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:27,103
Thank you.

131
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:32,317
Gosh, the weather is so nice.

132
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:34,986
By the way, Ms. Kim.

133
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:38,489
- Were you just somewhere?
- Sorry?

134
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:40,158
It looks like you were outside somewhere.

135
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,828
Oh, no. I came here right after waking up.

136
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:47,165
Oh, it's just that...

137
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:49,125
you look so radiant.

138
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:51,252
I see.

139
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,216
You! I told you not to do this!

140
00:11:57,091 --> 00:12:00,762
- What did I do?
- Look tired in front of the Chief Editor.

141
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:03,014
Don't you know the basic rule for writers?

142
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,974
Judging by your condition

143
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:07,727
it looks like
your manuscript is going well.

144
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,772
Oh, that's strange. That's not it at all.

145
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:14,150
I guess it's because I slept so well.

146
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:15,902
The water in Busan must be good.

147
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,654
I went to the sauna this morning too.

148
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,197
Don't I have a bit of a glow?

149
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:21,115
You're absolutely glowing.

150
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:22,992
Oops.

151
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:29,540
By the way, Shin PD...

152
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:31,376
said you're sharing a room...

153
00:12:31,626 --> 00:12:33,670
Yes. I tried to wake him

154
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:36,005
but he said he'll sleep in
and skip breakfast.

155
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:40,843
- I see.
- He's a night owl so he skips breakfast.

156
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,387
Oh, I see.

157
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:46,140
- Let me have some too.
- Of course.

158
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:48,726
Sushi. The sushi's good.

159
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:50,853
Got it.

160
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:00,905
I got all dressed up in my
"effortless style" for nothing.

161
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:03,783
Since Soon-rok isn't even here

162
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:06,703
let's eat till we burst.

163
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,498
Ms. Kim.

164
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:14,460
Did you have a good night?

165
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:21,092
It's Soon-rok.

166
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:23,052
Glad I chose the "effortless style."

167
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:25,013
He's so cute.

168
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:27,307
Look at his messy hair.

169
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:28,850
His T-shirt is so casual.

170
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,351
- He has great taste!
- Jeez!

171
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:33,062
He just looks like he woke up.
What's the fuss?

172
00:13:39,694 --> 00:13:41,362
You must like sushi, Ms. Kim.

173
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:47,452
Oh, the Chief Editor said
the sushi here is good.

174
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:48,745
I see.

175
00:13:49,287 --> 00:13:51,831
But I don't like sushi.

176
00:14:07,013 --> 00:14:09,849
So Soon-rok likes sausages.

177
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:12,518
He likes chicken too?

178
00:14:12,727 --> 00:14:14,354
He doesn't eat vegetables.

179
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:17,899
He has the palate of a kid.

180
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:19,859
Even his taste in food is cute.

181
00:14:28,034 --> 00:14:29,452
Is the chicken good?

182
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:36,918
I recommend it.

183
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:42,131
Even the way he speaks curtly is cute.

184
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,300
Gosh, what a cutie.

185
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,431
- Got it?
- Yes.

186
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:51,933
Let's go.

187
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:57,939
Hello.

188
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:01,859
Where's he going?

189
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:03,861
Oh, to buy some sandwiches.

190
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:06,030
For the people who skipped breakfast.

191
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:07,865
I think everyone will wake up late

192
00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:11,035
- so let's have free time until lunch.
- Sounds good.

193
00:15:13,788 --> 00:15:15,623
What will you do, Ms. Kim?

194
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,543
I'm going to take a walk.

195
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:21,879
I arrived late last night,
so I didn't get to see anything.

196
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:23,297
You should.

197
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:26,801
- You should enjoy the ocean view.
- I will.

198
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:28,261
I'm going to get some sleep.

199
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,429
Of course, go ahead.

200
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:51,200
I missed him. Darn it.

201
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:53,995
But he's nearby. Look for him.

202
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,480
Found him! I found Soon-rok!

203
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,904
Oh, there you are.

204
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:29,739
Ms. Kim.

205
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:32,700
I came out to buy coffee
and take a walk too.

206
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:34,160
I see.

207
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:36,204
- What would you like?
- No, I...

208
00:16:36,287 --> 00:16:38,748
No, I'm buying for all the writers.

209
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,124
What would you like?

210
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,835
Then...

211
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,796
a light Americano.

212
00:16:46,631 --> 00:16:48,341
I'll add one light Americano.

213
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:50,635
Yes!

214
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:52,470
That was very natural.

215
00:17:00,728 --> 00:17:03,147
- The gift you gave me...
- Yes?

216
00:17:03,231 --> 00:17:06,192
That café is in the spot
with the best view.

217
00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:07,777
Over there.

218
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:10,530
- I see.
- I'll visit before going to Seoul.

219
00:17:11,239 --> 00:17:12,406
In that case...

220
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:15,326
why don't we have a drink together?

221
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,579
- You were going for a walk, right?
- Yes.

222
00:17:18,746 --> 00:17:20,456
I'll show you a good route for your walk.

223
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,583
I found a great course last night.

224
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:24,544
Do you like walking at night?

225
00:17:25,336 --> 00:17:26,337
Yes.

226
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,673
I especially like the ocean at night.

227
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:31,217
I like the ocean at night too.

228
00:17:31,634 --> 00:17:33,177
Then why don't we...

229
00:17:33,261 --> 00:17:35,888
take a walk together tonight?

230
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:37,431
Rudolph.

231
00:17:37,932 --> 00:17:41,727
- Rudolph, your order's ready.
- It's ready.

232
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:45,856
What?

233
00:17:46,107 --> 00:17:47,775
His nickname is Rudolph?

234
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:50,945
Because his name is Soon-rok?

235
00:17:51,946 --> 00:17:54,240
How insanely cute. Rudolph?

236
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,784
Even his nickname is cute.

237
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:09,422
That morning

238
00:18:09,547 --> 00:18:12,341
Rudolph the Reindeer appeared.

239
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:20,224
- So cute!
- So cute!

240
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,896
Give me a break.

241
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,774
Yu-mi! Get a grip!

242
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:32,320
How old are you?
Why act like this over one emoticon?

243
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:34,280
Thank you.

244
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:39,118
Let me get that for you.

245
00:18:42,872 --> 00:18:44,040
By the way, may I ask...

246
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:46,375
when your birthday is?

247
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:49,503
- Sorry?
- Your birthday...

248
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:53,382
Oh, my birthday?

249
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:55,885
Yes.

250
00:18:56,427 --> 00:18:57,762
If you don't mind me asking.

251
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:00,514
There's no need to be so formal.

252
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:02,058
You can just ask casually.

253
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:04,393
But you're much older than me, aren't you?

254
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:09,607
If I may ask...

255
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:12,526
your age?

256
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:17,406
STRAWBERRY CREAM PUFF

257
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:21,285
EPISODE 11
THE ROAD TO SOMETHING MORE

258
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:24,705
Oh, my birthday?

259
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:26,457
Yes.

260
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:28,250
If you don't mind me asking.

261
00:19:28,626 --> 00:19:30,169
There's no need to be so formal.

262
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:32,046
You can just ask casually.

263
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,715
But you're much older than me, aren't you?

264
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:40,388
If I may ask...

265
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,140
your age?

266
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:48,604
BIRTHDAY

267
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:50,523
AGE

268
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:55,361
BIRTHDAY
AGE

269
00:19:57,405 --> 00:19:58,948
Hey, did you all hear that?

270
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,659
He asked about her birthday formally
like she's an old lady.

271
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,744
And her age, too!

272
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:06,205
Do you get it now?

273
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:08,499
How Soon-rok thinks of Yu-mi?

274
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:10,251
A relationship? Yeah, right.

275
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:13,337
Isn't that just what you say
to a writer who's older than you?

276
00:20:13,504 --> 00:20:15,464
If you have manners,
you should ask formally about birthdays.

277
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:17,633
And I think it's the same for age too.

278
00:20:17,842 --> 00:20:20,928
And Soon-rok is very professional.

279
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:22,263
Oh, please.

280
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:24,682
So you're saying it's okay?

281
00:20:28,102 --> 00:20:30,813
That's the first time someone's asked
for my age like that.

282
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:33,149
It's not like I'm a grandma or something.

283
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:35,776
Right...

284
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,446
I was going to ask how old you were

285
00:20:38,529 --> 00:20:41,615
- but that didn't seem right either.
- Why won't that be right?

286
00:20:41,699 --> 00:20:43,701
We're not that far apart in age.

287
00:20:44,118 --> 00:20:45,119
Really?

288
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:47,872
Then, what year were you born?

289
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:51,834
Say how old you are proudly!

290
00:20:57,298 --> 00:20:58,299
Take a guess.

291
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:00,384
As far as I know....

292
00:21:01,469 --> 00:21:02,470
It's 199...

293
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:07,391
- There you are, Shin PD.
- Mr. Kim.

294
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:08,934
Hey.

295
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:10,561
He's here.

296
00:21:14,148 --> 00:21:15,524
What a relief.

297
00:21:15,608 --> 00:21:17,526
We've changed the subject.

298
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:20,070
If she can't even tell him, it's hopeless.

299
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:22,615
How can she date him
with that little confidence?

300
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:25,534
Hey, do something about him.

301
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:27,453
He's such a killjoy. It's so annoying.

302
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:33,334
I didn't see you come yesterday.
When did you get here?

303
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:34,794
I arrived around 11:00 p.m.

304
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:36,420
- I see.
- Did you sleep well?

305
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:39,465
I couldn't sleep.
I was drinking until late last night.

306
00:21:40,591 --> 00:21:42,635
- Wait.
- You know her, right?

307
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:43,886
This is Writer Kim Yu-mi.

308
00:21:45,513 --> 00:21:47,139
Yes, of course I do.

309
00:21:47,598 --> 00:21:49,558
- Gosh, hello.
- Hello.

310
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:51,060
This is Writer Kim Ju-ho.

311
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:53,646
- Writer of The Invincible Baseball Team.
- Oh, hello.

312
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:55,356
It's a pleasure to meet you.

313
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:58,484
I've only seen your pictures,
but seeing you in person...

314
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:02,071
- You're so beautiful in person.
- Oh, thank you.

315
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:04,532
I'm not just saying that. I'm serious.

316
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:10,246
I was curious about you, since
The Invincible Baseball Team is popular.

317
00:22:11,622 --> 00:22:13,582
That's all in the past.
I'm planning to stop.

318
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,918
- I see.
- It should've ended a long time ago

319
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:18,462
but I need the money, so I'm stuck.

320
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:20,339
- Would you like some coffee?
- Yeah.

321
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:22,299
- I'll have an iced Americano.
- So this is where you were.

322
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:24,718
- You want coffee?
- No, I'm full.

323
00:22:24,802 --> 00:22:27,763
- Just have one. Two iced Americanos.
- Okay.

324
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:34,311
- Ms. Kim, this is Kim Ju-ho.
- We've already met.

325
00:22:39,942 --> 00:22:42,486
Shin PD is in charge of this team.

326
00:22:42,695 --> 00:22:44,655
- Oh, I see.
- That's right.

327
00:22:44,989 --> 00:22:49,243
You worked Soon-rok so hard
that he was taken off Yu-mi's team.

328
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:52,913
- Oh, really?
- Yeah. You should apologize.

329
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:56,083
Yu-mi is already so busy,
and you even took her PD away.

330
00:22:56,417 --> 00:22:58,586
It's okay if you take him.

331
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:00,671
Let me know if you need him.

332
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:02,590
The writer's manuscript comes first.

333
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:06,010
- Really?
- Of course.

334
00:23:06,427 --> 00:23:07,761
I've been writing this for so long

335
00:23:07,845 --> 00:23:09,305
I can write it with my toes now.

336
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:15,728
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

337
00:23:16,437 --> 00:23:18,105
- Then...
- Ms. Kim.

338
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:20,065
Don't believe him.

339
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:23,193
He gets generous only
when he doesn't have a deadline.

340
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:28,157
But later, he'll make a huge fuss,
asking who took our Shin PD.

341
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:30,951
Jeez, honestly. Good grief.

342
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:34,038
- Bingo!
- Goodness, stop doing that.

343
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:35,331
- What's with that guy?
- What's with that guy?

344
00:23:35,497 --> 00:23:36,498
Over here.

345
00:23:41,045 --> 00:23:43,464
Gosh, I like our Shin PD so much.

346
00:23:44,006 --> 00:23:47,176
- Thanks.
- But does Shin PD hate me?

347
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:49,219
Have some.

348
00:23:54,642 --> 00:23:55,893
Ju-ho is so fickle

349
00:23:55,976 --> 00:23:58,062
catering to his whims can't be easy.

350
00:23:58,646 --> 00:24:01,231
Hey. Shin PD doesn't cater to anyone.

351
00:24:01,315 --> 00:24:02,524
He just goes his own way.

352
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:03,984
He just plods along silently.

353
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:05,277
Look at him.

354
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:07,780
That's Shin PD's strong point.

355
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:11,116
He's got a strong backbone.

356
00:24:11,617 --> 00:24:12,785
- Chief Editor Ahn?
- Yeah.

357
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:13,953
Let's go in ten.

358
00:24:14,036 --> 00:24:15,829
- Everyone's at the lobby.
- Okay.

359
00:24:16,205 --> 00:24:17,665
We'll be leaving in ten minutes.

360
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:22,753
I see why Soon-rok is expressionless
when he works.

361
00:24:23,921 --> 00:24:25,339
I want to snatch Soon-rok away.

362
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:31,220
So Ms. Kim...

363
00:24:32,262 --> 00:24:34,473
You said you both
went to the same school, right?

364
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:38,352
- Yeah, we went to school together.
- I see.

365
00:24:38,644 --> 00:24:41,480
So you're from our generation then?

366
00:24:42,064 --> 00:24:43,857
Sorry, but what year did you start school?

367
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,151
Sorry?

368
00:24:46,986 --> 00:24:49,947
Wait. Why would you suddenly ask that?

369
00:24:50,114 --> 00:24:52,241
Change the subject!

370
00:24:52,783 --> 00:24:55,786
Well, didn't know we were alumni

371
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,621
and I found out at the publishing house.

372
00:24:58,497 --> 00:25:00,499
Oh my, that bread looks so delicious.

373
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:01,583
Should I buy some?

374
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:06,547
When I got out of the army,
she was a freshman...

375
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:08,590
So a three-year gap.

376
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:12,011
Then we're only four years apart?

377
00:25:12,428 --> 00:25:14,471
- Right.
- Hey...

378
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:19,184
For someone who looks so young,
you're surprisingly a bit old.

379
00:25:19,393 --> 00:25:21,020
- Jeez, cut it out.
- Oh, what?

380
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:24,857
The three of us can just be friends.

381
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:27,860
What?

382
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:29,987
Friends with a four-year age gap.

383
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:34,033
- What is he talking about?
- Never mind that, look!

384
00:25:36,744 --> 00:25:37,911
Soon-rok is...

385
00:25:38,078 --> 00:25:39,913
counting Yu-mi's age.

386
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:42,124
Is he one of those Gen Zs?

387
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:44,334
No, that's how you mess up
the whole social hierarchy.

388
00:25:56,263 --> 00:25:57,264
Jeez.

389
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:00,017
That writer talks too much.

390
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:02,144
It's draining my energy.

391
00:26:03,604 --> 00:26:05,689
The age gap is pretty big.

392
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:09,485
Right? It is.

393
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,362
Okay, I admit it.

394
00:26:16,492 --> 00:26:17,910
Is this even possible?

395
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:22,498
Even five years is already a big gap...

396
00:26:28,462 --> 00:26:29,963
You can't fall asleep, Yu-mi.

397
00:26:30,172 --> 00:26:31,673
You can't afford to sleep.

398
00:26:33,675 --> 00:26:35,302
Why did you come all the way to Busan?

399
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:40,140
It's not time to despair yet.

400
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,017
Love.

401
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:43,894
You didn't know he was younger?

402
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:47,147
I'm asking if you didn't know.

403
00:26:48,982 --> 00:26:49,983
Our Yu-mi

404
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,361
isn't an amateur anymore, right?

405
00:26:53,362 --> 00:26:54,738
Yu-mi is a pro.

406
00:26:55,364 --> 00:26:56,573
She may have gotten older

407
00:26:56,657 --> 00:26:59,368
- but she has experience and wisdom.
- And also...

408
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:01,578
her invincible, youthful skin.

409
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:11,255
What you do with Soon-rok today

410
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:12,798
can lead to something, Yu-mi

411
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:15,050
- Right? That's true.
- There's a chance.

412
00:27:15,134 --> 00:27:17,928
With confidence,
let's go for flirting stage!

413
00:27:18,011 --> 00:27:19,972
- Flirting stage!
- Flirting stage!

414
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:25,811
Should I text him and see
what he's doing after the meeting?

415
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:45,497
Hello?

416
00:27:45,581 --> 00:27:47,666
Hello, Ms. Kim. This is Kim Ju-ho.

417
00:27:48,709 --> 00:27:49,710
Sorry?

418
00:27:50,627 --> 00:27:51,628
Oh, right.

419
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:54,798
- Hello.
- What are you doing now?

420
00:27:55,424 --> 00:27:56,425
Right now?

421
00:27:58,552 --> 00:27:59,678
Nothing much.

422
00:28:00,345 --> 00:28:01,471
I see.

423
00:28:01,889 --> 00:28:05,017
Well, we're not having lunch
until one o'clock.

424
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,435
We have a lot of time left, you know.

425
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:10,189
So for research, I was thinking
of going to Bosu-dong Book Street.

426
00:28:10,939 --> 00:28:11,940
Would you like to go together?

427
00:28:12,566 --> 00:28:14,526
Bosu-dong Book Street?

428
00:28:14,985 --> 00:28:17,529
Yes. We should have
just enough time if we take a taxi.

429
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:20,365
Let's go together and just browse.

430
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:22,117
There are a lot of books there.

431
00:28:22,201 --> 00:28:24,077
I'm sure you'll like it there.

432
00:28:25,495 --> 00:28:27,664
Well, I'm not really...

433
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:29,041
Shin PD.

434
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:31,168
Two hours is enough
to look around and come back, right?

435
00:28:32,002 --> 00:28:34,254
Yes, two hours is more than enough.

436
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:37,049
Wait, Soon-rok is going too?

437
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,802
If you go, who's going?

438
00:28:41,678 --> 00:28:44,264
Me, Shin PD...

439
00:28:46,225 --> 00:28:48,393
Dae-yong said he's busy, so he can't go.

440
00:28:49,186 --> 00:28:52,189
- I see.
- Great!

441
00:28:52,356 --> 00:28:53,607
Let's go!

442
00:28:54,233 --> 00:28:55,651
Come on, let's go together.

443
00:28:55,943 --> 00:28:58,487
You might get some ideas.

444
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:00,364
- Who is he talking to?
- Ms. Kim.

445
00:29:04,868 --> 00:29:06,161
In that case...

446
00:29:06,411 --> 00:29:07,412
should I?

447
00:29:07,496 --> 00:29:10,749
I didn't have anything else to do anyway.

448
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,876
And I've wanted to visit Bosu-dong.

449
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:17,339
All right.

450
00:29:17,422 --> 00:29:20,300
- See you in the lobby in ten minutes.
- Okay.

451
00:29:33,230 --> 00:29:36,149
Great! We're meeting again naturally.

452
00:29:36,233 --> 00:29:38,652
But Mr. Kim is in the way.

453
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:41,738
It's more natural
to have someone else there.

454
00:29:41,905 --> 00:29:44,908
You need a third party
during the "flirting" phase.

455
00:29:45,117 --> 00:29:48,787
That's experience and wisdom for you.

456
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:51,373
Shin PD, you should get a taxi.

457
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:52,916
Yes, I'm booking one now.

458
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:56,003
- She said she's coming.
- Really?

459
00:29:56,086 --> 00:29:57,087
Yeah.

460
00:29:57,379 --> 00:30:00,090
Hey, you're sure Ms. Kim
doesn't have a boyfriend, right?

461
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:04,094
No. She's my wife's best friend.
I'm positive.

462
00:30:04,678 --> 00:30:05,971
Okay.

463
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:13,061
Wait. Get the taxi.

464
00:30:13,562 --> 00:30:14,938
I'm just going to my room for a second.

465
00:30:16,106 --> 00:30:18,233
- Work hard.
- Yes, I'll see you later.

466
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,413
Shin PD.

467
00:30:32,706 --> 00:30:33,707
Ms. Kim.

468
00:30:34,708 --> 00:30:36,418
-Where's Mr. Kim?
-Getting his camera.

469
00:30:36,710 --> 00:30:37,711
He'll be back soon.

470
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:42,924
By the way, aren't you tired?

471
00:30:43,759 --> 00:30:47,387
- Sorry?
- You got in late and got up early...

472
00:30:47,721 --> 00:30:49,931
If you're tired, you don't have to
force yourself to go.

473
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:52,225
No, I'm fine.

474
00:30:53,101 --> 00:30:56,813
If you feel obligated to go,
I can talk to Mr. Kim for you.

475
00:30:56,938 --> 00:30:58,357
Please, no need.

476
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:01,360
It's just that I think
it would be good to go.

477
00:31:01,485 --> 00:31:04,071
- I can use it in my manuscript.
- Busan?

478
00:31:04,863 --> 00:31:06,490
Is Busan in your manuscript?

479
00:31:08,408 --> 00:31:09,576
Yes, well...

480
00:31:09,993 --> 00:31:11,161
I think it will be soon.

481
00:31:11,995 --> 00:31:13,372
What happens in Busan?

482
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,043
I'm still thinking about it.

483
00:31:18,835 --> 00:31:22,005
The female lead goes on a trip
to Busan by herself

484
00:31:22,297 --> 00:31:23,465
Even though

485
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:25,717
she has a travel phobia?

486
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:30,389
Can you please stop prying so much?

487
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:32,599
Stop nitpicking.

488
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:35,185
Because I want to be with you, okay?

489
00:31:35,519 --> 00:31:37,813
Do I really have to spell it out?

490
00:31:42,025 --> 00:31:43,693
Well...

491
00:31:45,987 --> 00:31:47,030
The taxi's here.

492
00:31:49,616 --> 00:31:50,617
Shin PD!

493
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:53,912
Hello, Ms. Kim.

494
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:56,248
- Is that our taxi?
- Yes.

495
00:31:57,541 --> 00:31:58,542
Let's go.

496
00:31:59,167 --> 00:32:00,168
Go, go.

497
00:32:11,513 --> 00:32:12,639
Ms. Kim.

498
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:14,391
Do you come to Busan often?

499
00:32:15,684 --> 00:32:16,685
No.

500
00:32:16,977 --> 00:32:19,813
I think I've been here
about three or four times.

501
00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:24,234
I used to come here really often
when I was young.

502
00:32:24,693 --> 00:32:26,445
My town had no baseball team

503
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:28,196
so I liked Busan's Cougars team.

504
00:32:28,447 --> 00:32:30,073
- Right.
- Gosh.

505
00:32:30,157 --> 00:32:33,702
I wanted to watch baseball back then,
but I had no money.

506
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:38,290
I couldn't take the Tongil-ho train.
I had to take the Bidulgi-ho.

507
00:32:39,082 --> 00:32:41,668
The Bidulgi-ho must've taken forever.

508
00:32:41,877 --> 00:32:45,881
Exactly. We'd kill time
talking with friends on the train.

509
00:32:49,509 --> 00:32:50,552
I knew it.

510
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:55,098
- Sorry?
- I knew we were kindred spirits.

511
00:32:55,849 --> 00:32:58,351
You know about the Bidulgi-ho.

512
00:32:58,602 --> 00:33:00,061
I bet Shin PD doesn't know about it.

513
00:33:00,353 --> 00:33:01,688
Do you know what the Bidulgi-ho is?

514
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:04,733
- The Bidulgi-ho?
- You don't, do you?

515
00:33:06,526 --> 00:33:07,569
Is it the name of a ship?

516
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,616
See? His generation has no idea.

517
00:33:13,575 --> 00:33:16,828
We were the last generation
to ride the Bidulgi-ho.

518
00:33:16,912 --> 00:33:18,413
Was that around the year 2000?

519
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:20,457
It went out of service around then.

520
00:33:20,874 --> 00:33:22,792
See? We're kindred spirits.

521
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:28,381
Friends, right?

522
00:33:28,465 --> 00:33:29,466
Friends.

523
00:33:30,967 --> 00:33:32,302
Bidulgi-ho?

524
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:34,387
Gosh.

525
00:33:34,471 --> 00:33:36,515
We're totally contemporaries.

526
00:33:37,224 --> 00:33:38,475
Not really.

527
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:43,480
Hey, that writer is so annoying.

528
00:33:43,730 --> 00:33:47,692
Why does he put me in his generation?
Especially in front of Soon-rok.

529
00:33:47,776 --> 00:33:49,194
Don't get swept up in this.

530
00:33:49,486 --> 00:33:52,322
If he brings up the old days again,
let's just not respond.

531
00:33:52,405 --> 00:33:56,660
- Guys, we're in big trouble.
- Why?

532
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:59,788
The place we're at right now...

533
00:33:59,913 --> 00:34:02,707
is a haven for nostalgia.

534
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:08,630
Gosh...

535
00:34:10,674 --> 00:34:12,509
This is Bosu-dong Book Street.

536
00:34:12,759 --> 00:34:15,095
There are so many books here.

537
00:34:21,685 --> 00:34:23,061
This place is amazing.

538
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:29,818
Look at these magazines. Gosh.

539
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:33,613
Oh, look at this! Gukjin Bread! Ms. Kim.

540
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:35,490
You know what this is, right?
Gukjin Bread.

541
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:38,910
Wow, I really loved Gukjin Bread.

542
00:34:39,369 --> 00:34:42,497
You know, right? We'd take stickers
and ditch the bread.

543
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:45,000
Of course, I do.

544
00:34:45,125 --> 00:34:47,335
I bought so many just for the stickers.

545
00:34:47,419 --> 00:34:50,005
And you'd always get the same sticker
over and over again.

546
00:34:50,297 --> 00:34:52,340
But wait, does Shin PD know this?

547
00:34:54,134 --> 00:34:55,135
I've never seen it before.

548
00:34:55,218 --> 00:34:56,678
Is it bread made
by the comedian Kim Gook-jin?

549
00:34:59,639 --> 00:35:00,640
Kim Gook-jin?

550
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:03,226
See? He has no idea.

551
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:05,478
I'm telling you,
his generation's different from ours.

552
00:35:06,479 --> 00:35:07,480
But...

553
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:09,441
I don't know either.

554
00:35:09,899 --> 00:35:12,152
What? No way you wouldn't know.

555
00:35:12,819 --> 00:35:15,530
No, I really don't know.

556
00:35:15,864 --> 00:35:18,033
Was it popular in your generation?

557
00:35:18,825 --> 00:35:20,493
We're from the same generation.

558
00:35:20,702 --> 00:35:22,078
We're different.

559
00:35:22,162 --> 00:35:23,371
We're obviously different.

560
00:35:26,333 --> 00:35:27,417
Come on.

561
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,878
We're from the same generation. Ms. Kim!

562
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:34,758
Let's just browse quickly
and get out of here.

563
00:35:34,841 --> 00:35:38,178
If we stay, I'll be stuck in this
hell of forced generational bonding.

564
00:35:38,303 --> 00:35:42,265
MORE PEOPLE ARE MADE BY BOOKS
THAN BOOKS ARE MADE BY PEOPLE

565
00:35:53,526 --> 00:35:55,945
I really like this street.
The atmosphere is great.

566
00:35:57,072 --> 00:36:00,492
It would've been so nice
if I'd come here with just Soon-rok.

567
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:07,248
But where's Soon-rok?

568
00:36:23,682 --> 00:36:24,933
You know this, right?

569
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:27,352
Guiyeoni.

570
00:36:27,852 --> 00:36:29,771
Wow, they have this book here.

571
00:36:29,979 --> 00:36:31,898
I mean, Guiyeoni is practically

572
00:36:32,107 --> 00:36:35,443
our foremother, isn't she?

573
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:38,321
Well, I don't really know.

574
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,407
Come on, don't lie. No way.

575
00:36:40,490 --> 00:36:43,201
I told you
we're from different generations.

576
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:47,789
But where did Shin PD go? I don't see him.

577
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,126
Shin PD left early.

578
00:36:52,711 --> 00:36:56,464
- What? Where to?
- He had to go and left.

579
00:36:58,675 --> 00:37:01,469
- But...
- Ms. Kim, you must be hungry.

580
00:37:01,845 --> 00:37:04,806
Should we grab a quick
and delicious bite nearby?

581
00:37:07,517 --> 00:37:09,269
- Well...
- Huh?

582
00:37:26,369 --> 00:37:28,496
- Hello?
- Where are you?

583
00:37:28,621 --> 00:37:30,081
I'm on my way back to the hotel.

584
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:31,958
- All three of you?
- No.

585
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:33,710
It's just me.

586
00:37:34,711 --> 00:37:35,712
Just you?

587
00:37:36,129 --> 00:37:37,756
He told me to go.

588
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:42,302
Gosh, that guy. All right.

589
00:38:10,205 --> 00:38:12,415
Hello? Hey Ida.

590
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:14,542
Why are you calling?

591
00:38:15,835 --> 00:38:16,920
Are you resting well?

592
00:38:17,504 --> 00:38:20,381
- Are you having fun?
- Fun? I'm tired.

593
00:38:20,799 --> 00:38:21,800
By the way.

594
00:38:22,425 --> 00:38:24,219
You met that writer, Kim Ju-ho, right?

595
00:38:25,345 --> 00:38:26,387
How is he?

596
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:28,556
What do you mean, "How is he?"

597
00:38:28,681 --> 00:38:31,684
Dae-yong says Kim Ju-ho is a fan of yours.

598
00:38:32,101 --> 00:38:34,395
He's apparently been asking
to be introduced for a long time.

599
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,523
- You met him there, right?
- I did.

600
00:38:36,773 --> 00:38:37,774
How was he? How was he?

601
00:38:38,024 --> 00:38:39,359
I've met him a few times.

602
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:41,110
He's fun and likable.

603
00:38:41,611 --> 00:38:43,863
- Did you all conspire against me?
- What?

604
00:38:44,197 --> 00:38:47,408
It looks like you all plotted
to set me up with him.

605
00:38:47,826 --> 00:38:50,078
He suggested we do some research

606
00:38:50,286 --> 00:38:52,455
but then the PD just disappeared.

607
00:38:53,665 --> 00:38:57,502
- Oh my.
- So we had lunch and coffee alone.

608
00:38:57,585 --> 00:39:00,171
- On our first meeting, like a date.
- Really?

609
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:03,508
You? Just the two of you?

610
00:39:03,591 --> 00:39:06,261
Why is everyone so desperate
to set me up with someone?

611
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:08,555
Come on, what are you talking about?

612
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:11,140
He earns good money

613
00:39:11,432 --> 00:39:12,767
your ages are compatible

614
00:39:12,934 --> 00:39:15,895
and since you have the same job,
you'd understand each other well.

615
00:39:16,104 --> 00:39:17,272
That's what we were thinking.

616
00:39:18,815 --> 00:39:19,858
I see.

617
00:39:21,067 --> 00:39:22,235
Your ages are compatible.

618
00:39:22,861 --> 00:39:24,153
You're compatible in many ways.

619
00:39:25,488 --> 00:39:27,699
Since it seemed like we're
compatible in many ways

620
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:29,868
the PD also made himself scarce.

621
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:31,244
That's what it is.

622
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:33,371
So...

623
00:39:33,454 --> 00:39:36,624
- You don't like him?
- It's not that I don't like him.

624
00:39:37,917 --> 00:39:38,918
Never mind.

625
00:39:39,252 --> 00:39:42,046
Who am I to say whether I like him or not?

626
00:39:43,464 --> 00:39:44,465
Never mind.

627
00:39:44,757 --> 00:39:45,884
All right then.

628
00:39:46,885 --> 00:39:47,886
Okay, bye.

629
00:39:52,765 --> 00:39:55,310
Gosh, why did I come all the way to Busan?

630
00:39:55,602 --> 00:39:56,644
Jeez.

631
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:08,948
Yes, Jang PD.

632
00:40:09,282 --> 00:40:11,576
Ms. Kim, I haven't seen you all day.

633
00:40:12,368 --> 00:40:14,245
I know. I was a bit busy.

634
00:40:14,579 --> 00:40:15,580
Come on down.

635
00:40:15,997 --> 00:40:17,415
We're going to dinner soon.

636
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,083
Yes, I'll be right there.

637
00:40:28,343 --> 00:40:29,552
Well, I've got to eat.

638
00:40:41,606 --> 00:40:44,025
They were together all day
and just came in a little while ago.

639
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:45,818
I wonder if it's going well.

640
00:40:46,778 --> 00:40:48,196
What? Are they talking about me again?

641
00:40:48,655 --> 00:40:50,365
Why is everyone acting like this?

642
00:40:50,782 --> 00:40:54,619
I mean, he was just so excited.

643
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:56,120
Really?

644
00:41:01,501 --> 00:41:02,502
The nerve.

645
00:41:02,752 --> 00:41:04,128
Who does he think he is?

646
00:41:04,253 --> 00:41:05,254
But don't you think

647
00:41:05,421 --> 00:41:07,006
they look good together?

648
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:13,304
Not really.

649
00:41:13,930 --> 00:41:14,931
What?

650
00:41:15,056 --> 00:41:16,641
They don't look good together.

651
00:41:16,766 --> 00:41:17,767
You don't think so?

652
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:19,477
Why? Don't they look good together?

653
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:32,156
EPISODE 12
IS THERE A CHANCE?

654
00:41:32,949 --> 00:41:34,534
They don't look good together.

655
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:35,952
You don't think so?

656
00:41:36,119 --> 00:41:37,537
Why? Don't they look good together?

657
00:41:38,246 --> 00:41:39,247
No.

658
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:41,290
They don't.

659
00:41:48,047 --> 00:41:49,257
Why? What is it?

660
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:50,758
What about them doesn't match?

661
00:41:54,887 --> 00:41:55,972
Chief Editor Ahn.

662
00:41:58,641 --> 00:42:00,727
- Oh, you're here?
- You're here.

663
00:42:01,019 --> 00:42:02,145
How was fishing?

664
00:42:03,062 --> 00:42:04,647
- Hi, Yu-mi!
- Jang PD.

665
00:42:04,731 --> 00:42:06,899
Gosh, it's so hard to see you.

666
00:42:06,983 --> 00:42:09,861
No, I was just looking for you.

667
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:13,239
Say hello. This is Writer Kim Yu-mi.

668
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:15,116
And this is Writer Bae Woo-joo.

669
00:42:15,283 --> 00:42:16,826
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

670
00:42:16,993 --> 00:42:20,246
- I'm a big fan.
- Thank you.

671
00:42:21,372 --> 00:42:23,499
- Everyone's over there. Let's go.
- Okay.

672
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:25,043
- Okay.
- Let's go.

673
00:42:25,126 --> 00:42:27,378
- Hello.
- Oh, you're here?

674
00:42:27,462 --> 00:42:28,755
- Oh, it's nice to meet you.
- Writer Bae Woo-joo.

675
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,632
- Say hello.
- It's our first time meeting.

676
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:33,134
- Ah, so it is.
- Yes.

677
00:43:00,745 --> 00:43:01,746
It's big here.

678
00:43:01,829 --> 00:43:02,955
Right this way.

679
00:43:05,458 --> 00:43:07,043
- What about the other teams?
- They're all here.

680
00:43:12,715 --> 00:43:15,968
- The restroom...
- It's one floor up, Ms. Kim.

681
00:43:16,594 --> 00:43:17,595
Thank you.

682
00:43:18,221 --> 00:43:19,263
- Let's go.
- Sure.

683
00:43:30,149 --> 00:43:32,401
Coming to Busan was a good idea, right?

684
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:35,071
Of course. It was a great idea.

685
00:43:36,989 --> 00:43:37,990
It was.

686
00:43:42,662 --> 00:43:44,038
Oh, come on.

687
00:43:45,206 --> 00:43:46,415
Hey, Ms. Yu-mi!

688
00:43:47,208 --> 00:43:48,292
Over here.

689
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:50,711
Ms. Kim, come over here.

690
00:43:52,672 --> 00:43:54,841
Wait, that seat looks dangerous.

691
00:43:55,216 --> 00:43:56,425
Ms. Kim, this way.

692
00:43:56,509 --> 00:43:58,344
There's a seat here.

693
00:43:59,637 --> 00:44:01,973
It's dangerous.
They're from a similar generation.

694
00:44:02,223 --> 00:44:05,601
- I'll sit here...
- Come on, go ahead.

695
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:08,146
This is by the door,
so we'll be going in and out.

696
00:44:09,063 --> 00:44:10,106
Over here, Ms. Kim.

697
00:44:10,189 --> 00:44:12,859
- Yes, come here.
- This way.

698
00:44:17,697 --> 00:44:19,949
Hey, Ms. Kim is here.

699
00:44:23,786 --> 00:44:26,956
I was waiting for you
and saved you a seat.

700
00:44:27,498 --> 00:44:29,375
This is the seat of honor.

701
00:44:30,168 --> 00:44:31,169
Thank you.

702
00:44:31,377 --> 00:44:33,171
Hello, Ms. Kim.

703
00:44:33,254 --> 00:44:35,506
- Hello.
- I'm so happy to finally see you.

704
00:44:36,799 --> 00:44:38,134
But this is strange.

705
00:44:38,467 --> 00:44:41,262
He definitely said
it was the seat of honor.

706
00:44:41,929 --> 00:44:43,055
It's not the seat of honor

707
00:44:43,723 --> 00:44:45,141
it's the old-timers' seat, isn't it?

708
00:44:47,894 --> 00:44:48,936
Bingo!

709
00:44:49,228 --> 00:44:54,192
This is a seat for people
who remember the Bidulgi-ho train.

710
00:44:54,859 --> 00:44:57,403
What a load of nonsense.

711
00:44:57,862 --> 00:45:01,532
- Kids don't know the Bidulgi-ho?
- They don't.

712
00:45:01,616 --> 00:45:03,659
Besides the four of us, no one knows.

713
00:45:08,956 --> 00:45:10,208
This is crazy.

714
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:12,919
The hell of generational bonding
has begun again.

715
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:14,921
Oh, really?

716
00:45:17,506 --> 00:45:18,507
Thanks for your hard work.

717
00:45:18,591 --> 00:45:20,218
- It was nothing.
- You worked hard.

718
00:45:22,303 --> 00:45:25,014
- Let's cheers.
- You worked hard.

719
00:45:27,225 --> 00:45:28,643
Thank you.

720
00:45:33,689 --> 00:45:35,149
Excuse me.

721
00:45:35,358 --> 00:45:36,943
I'd like to...

722
00:45:37,401 --> 00:45:39,195
say a few words.

723
00:45:39,904 --> 00:45:45,326
It's not easy to get all you writers
together in one place

724
00:45:45,493 --> 00:45:48,663
so today is truly a moving day.

725
00:45:48,913 --> 00:45:53,376
Of course, while some of you
know each other well

726
00:45:53,584 --> 00:45:56,254
there are those
who are meeting for the first time

727
00:45:56,337 --> 00:45:58,381
even though we're from the same publisher.

728
00:45:58,547 --> 00:46:02,009
So I'd like to introduce
everyone one by one.

729
00:46:02,343 --> 00:46:05,179
Who should I start with...

730
00:46:06,555 --> 00:46:08,891
What about the order of
when we entered college?

731
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:10,685
- Sit down.
- Okay.

732
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:14,397
Okay, then let's start with Isabelle.

733
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:19,986
That guy, he's starting again. I'm so mad!

734
00:46:20,069 --> 00:46:22,697
If we go by this order, Yu-mi is fourth!

735
00:46:23,948 --> 00:46:26,033
Why me again?

736
00:46:26,450 --> 00:46:28,661
I won't go first
unless it's for a beauty ranking.

737
00:46:28,744 --> 00:46:31,664
Why are we ranking people
all the way here?

738
00:46:31,747 --> 00:46:33,541
Let's just do it freely, freely.

739
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,835
Just freestyle. Freely.

740
00:46:36,544 --> 00:46:37,545
Freely?

741
00:46:37,628 --> 00:46:38,963
I'll just go first.

742
00:46:42,383 --> 00:46:45,553
Hello, I'm Writer Kim Yu-mi.

743
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:49,223
It's a real pleasure
to meet you all like this.

744
00:46:55,771 --> 00:46:57,690
Ms. Kim is so cool.

745
00:47:09,076 --> 00:47:11,454
So you are an only daughter?

746
00:47:11,537 --> 00:47:12,705
Yes, an only daughter.

747
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:15,166
I'm the youngest of five siblings.

748
00:47:15,541 --> 00:47:17,460
I have three older sisters
and one older brother.

749
00:47:17,793 --> 00:47:19,712
Oh, I see.

750
00:47:20,588 --> 00:47:22,631
But how did you go from working

751
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:24,633
at a noodle company to writing?

752
00:47:24,925 --> 00:47:26,886
I originally studied creative writing

753
00:47:27,094 --> 00:47:29,597
so I wasn't good at anything
other than writing.

754
00:47:30,014 --> 00:47:32,516
But if you were in finance

755
00:47:32,933 --> 00:47:34,852
isn't that a bit far from writing?

756
00:47:36,437 --> 00:47:38,105
It's a long story

757
00:47:38,439 --> 00:47:41,317
and it's a boring one.
You know how it goes.

758
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:43,277
- Ms. Kim.
- "How it goes."

759
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:45,654
Do you remember that time? You know.

760
00:47:45,946 --> 00:47:48,074
After that play in Daehangno

761
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:50,826
the Chief Editor, you, and me,

762
00:47:50,910 --> 00:47:52,536
we had some drinks.

763
00:47:52,787 --> 00:47:54,330
We went home

764
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:56,916
- on all fours.
- This isn't it.

765
00:47:56,999 --> 00:47:58,584
It's too far to get close.

766
00:47:59,502 --> 00:48:00,795
Today's a lost cause.

767
00:48:01,128 --> 00:48:02,171
Let's give up.

768
00:48:02,797 --> 00:48:06,258
Everyone, wouldn't it be better
to just go to sleep?

769
00:48:06,634 --> 00:48:08,636
Yu-mi is so tired.

770
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:12,515
-I walked on two feet.
-You were like a puppy.

771
00:48:12,598 --> 00:48:14,058
- A dog.
- Oh, come on.

772
00:48:14,892 --> 00:48:17,061
Wait, where are you going?

773
00:48:17,937 --> 00:48:22,483
- I'm just going to the restroom.
- With your bag and everything?

774
00:48:25,403 --> 00:48:28,447
You're quite interested in my business.

775
00:48:29,865 --> 00:48:31,367
Oh, yes. Go ahead.

776
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:38,791
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

777
00:48:46,048 --> 00:48:47,174
Ms. Kim.

778
00:48:49,343 --> 00:48:50,386
Where are you going?

779
00:48:51,345 --> 00:48:52,972
Well, I...

780
00:48:53,681 --> 00:48:55,141
Is it okay if I slip out?

781
00:48:55,349 --> 00:48:57,309
Oh, are you going to the hotel?

782
00:48:57,435 --> 00:48:59,854
Yes, I've said my hellos

783
00:49:00,354 --> 00:49:03,023
and I'm so tired
from walking around all day.

784
00:49:03,607 --> 00:49:04,608
Go ahead, then.

785
00:49:05,609 --> 00:49:08,654
Everyone's going for round two.
I think they'll be a while.

786
00:49:09,655 --> 00:49:13,367
- Oh, then I'll take you.
- No, it's okay. It's right there.

787
00:49:13,451 --> 00:49:14,827
But still.

788
00:49:15,327 --> 00:49:16,328
It's fine.

789
00:49:16,412 --> 00:49:18,456
Jang PD, you'd have to come back alone.

790
00:49:18,998 --> 00:49:21,417
I want to walk. Have fun.

791
00:49:33,471 --> 00:49:36,724
We're together, but we can't be together.

792
00:49:37,057 --> 00:49:38,517
This is hard.

793
00:49:39,435 --> 00:49:41,187
There's no chance
to even make eye contact.

794
00:49:41,270 --> 00:49:43,147
Because Soon-rok isn't looking.

795
00:49:43,439 --> 00:49:44,982
He's not looking at Yu-mi.

796
00:49:45,733 --> 00:49:47,151
Because he's working.

797
00:49:47,318 --> 00:49:49,612
Soon-rok is strict about separating
his public and private life.

798
00:49:49,778 --> 00:49:51,780
Separating public and private life? Sure.

799
00:49:52,072 --> 00:49:55,409
If he's so strict, would he leave
just because Ju-ho said to?

800
00:49:55,618 --> 00:49:57,661
Didn't you hear him say
they don't look good together?

801
00:49:57,786 --> 00:50:00,039
He said that because they don't.

802
00:50:00,247 --> 00:50:01,248
Don't you know Soon-rok?

803
00:50:01,499 --> 00:50:03,459
He's the type to only state facts.

804
00:50:04,543 --> 00:50:06,712
Can't you just be quiet for a bit?

805
00:50:07,046 --> 00:50:08,881
You're the one who should watch yourself.

806
00:50:08,964 --> 00:50:10,466
It's just a one-sided crush anyway.

807
00:50:10,633 --> 00:50:13,260
It's a relationship that will end
before it even becomes anything.

808
00:50:13,969 --> 00:50:15,137
What do you know?

809
00:50:15,596 --> 00:50:18,224
Hey, Yu-mi is a romance writer.

810
00:50:19,517 --> 00:50:21,393
Don't you know the formula
for romance novels?

811
00:50:22,561 --> 00:50:25,814
They have to give you an opening
to get past a one-sided crush.

812
00:50:28,192 --> 00:50:29,193
Watch closely.

813
00:50:29,527 --> 00:50:32,613
In a one-sided crush,
if they give some hope

814
00:50:32,821 --> 00:50:34,448
it evolves into a flirting stage.

815
00:50:34,532 --> 00:50:35,991
but if they don't

816
00:50:36,242 --> 00:50:37,910
it just stays a one-sided crush.

817
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:41,539
- An opening?
- Yes, an opening.

818
00:50:41,914 --> 00:50:43,082
Look at Kim Ju-ho!

819
00:50:44,124 --> 00:50:46,961
If you're not hungry,
how about just a cool drink then?

820
00:50:47,044 --> 00:50:48,879
- His attitude when they're alone.
- A cool one.

821
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:51,799
Ms. Kim!

822
00:50:51,924 --> 00:50:54,635
- His effort to sit beside her.
- Come over here.

823
00:50:55,177 --> 00:50:57,263
So you are an only daughter?

824
00:50:57,388 --> 00:50:59,390
His curiosity and questions about Yu-mi.

825
00:51:00,724 --> 00:51:03,102
That's exactly what an opening is.

826
00:51:03,352 --> 00:51:05,521
The kind of things Kim Ju-ho gives.

827
00:51:05,854 --> 00:51:07,982
Has Soon-rok ever given you
something like that?

828
00:51:08,232 --> 00:51:09,275
Has he?

829
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:17,908
His attitude when they're alone.

830
00:51:19,243 --> 00:51:20,286
It's all right.

831
00:51:20,369 --> 00:51:21,620
My seat is over there.

832
00:51:22,705 --> 00:51:24,373
I couldn't get seats next to each other.

833
00:51:25,457 --> 00:51:28,043
His effort to sit with her no matter what.

834
00:51:28,544 --> 00:51:29,962
Oh, I see.

835
00:51:30,254 --> 00:51:31,839
Oh, right.

836
00:51:32,089 --> 00:51:33,090
Yes.

837
00:51:33,173 --> 00:51:34,675
Yes.

838
00:51:35,134 --> 00:51:36,260
Oh, I see.

839
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:40,681
His curiosity and questions about Yu-mi.

840
00:51:41,932 --> 00:51:44,018
Has Shin PD ever done something like this?

841
00:51:44,268 --> 00:51:45,311
Has he?

842
00:51:46,478 --> 00:51:48,814
He hasn't. Not even once.

843
00:51:49,732 --> 00:51:50,858
Right.

844
00:51:51,025 --> 00:51:55,946
It means Shin PD isn't interested
in Yu-mi as a woman.

845
00:51:56,196 --> 00:51:58,407
He said they don't look good together
because they don't.

846
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:02,578
- So we don't have a chance...
- Ms. Kim.

847
00:52:09,043 --> 00:52:10,169
Sh... Shin PD.

848
00:52:13,964 --> 00:52:16,300
Jang PD was worried

849
00:52:16,634 --> 00:52:17,760
that you left by yourself.

850
00:52:19,637 --> 00:52:20,929
But I'm almost there.

851
00:52:22,181 --> 00:52:23,432
I know.

852
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:24,933
I was too late.

853
00:52:27,269 --> 00:52:28,729
It's right around the corner.

854
00:52:28,812 --> 00:52:30,648
Still, it's nighttime.

855
00:52:33,859 --> 00:52:35,944
This is an opening.

856
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:37,696
It's not an opening.

857
00:52:37,780 --> 00:52:38,864
It is an opening.

858
00:52:39,073 --> 00:52:40,074
Ask him.

859
00:52:42,201 --> 00:52:43,243
It's an excuse, right?

860
00:52:44,912 --> 00:52:48,123
Didn't you volunteer to escort me
because you wanted to leave?

861
00:52:50,125 --> 00:52:51,168
Well...

862
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:55,005
I can't deny that.

863
00:52:58,092 --> 00:52:59,093
See?

864
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:04,306
The writers here are heavy drinkers

865
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:06,725
so it's a bit overwhelming.

866
00:53:07,309 --> 00:53:09,478
I understand. It is overwhelming.

867
00:53:10,521 --> 00:53:11,563
Yes.

868
00:53:14,775 --> 00:53:15,776
Let's go.

869
00:53:16,068 --> 00:53:17,069
Okay.

870
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:27,663
- Going up.
- Please get some rest.

871
00:53:29,665 --> 00:53:30,708
Aren't you going up?

872
00:53:30,833 --> 00:53:32,543
No, I can't sleep.

873
00:53:33,419 --> 00:53:34,586
What are you going to do?

874
00:53:35,462 --> 00:53:36,588
I'm thinking of watching a movie.

875
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:38,173
There's a theater right in front.

876
00:53:39,383 --> 00:53:41,593
- What movie...
- Thomas' Game.

877
00:53:42,052 --> 00:53:44,221
I was planning to see it
because it's a James King original.

878
00:53:45,264 --> 00:53:47,975
- I really like James King too.
- I see.

879
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:52,396
I can't focus in crowded theaters,
so I planned to go before it ends.

880
00:53:53,439 --> 00:53:55,357
But it turns out today
is the last day it's showing.

881
00:53:56,275 --> 00:53:57,276
I see.

882
00:53:58,068 --> 00:53:59,528
Well, enjoy your rest.

883
00:54:00,237 --> 00:54:02,406
- Thank you. Enjoy the movie.
- Thank you.

884
00:54:03,991 --> 00:54:05,284
Door closing.

885
00:54:14,418 --> 00:54:16,628
Isn't this a real opening?

886
00:54:18,005 --> 00:54:20,424
He's explaining the movie
in too much detail.

887
00:54:20,507 --> 00:54:22,760
- Does he really need to do that?
- That's true.

888
00:54:23,969 --> 00:54:25,471
Doesn't that mean it's okay
to go with him?

889
00:54:26,221 --> 00:54:27,556
Let's ask to go with him.

890
00:54:27,639 --> 00:54:29,808
Say that Yu-mi wanted
to see that movie too.

891
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:31,852
Isn't that too obvious?

892
00:54:31,935 --> 00:54:34,354
But what if it's not an opening...

893
00:54:34,438 --> 00:54:36,732
I told you it's not an opening!

894
00:54:37,816 --> 00:54:39,610
There's no need to listen to cowards.

895
00:54:40,194 --> 00:54:42,613
We have to be brave
when faced with an opportunity.

896
00:54:42,988 --> 00:54:46,116
If Soon-rok gave you an opening,
you have to respond.

897
00:55:07,679 --> 00:55:09,640
- Hello?
- Shin PD.

898
00:55:09,807 --> 00:55:11,517
- It's me.
- Yes, Ms. Kim.

899
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:14,603
Did you arrive at the theater?

900
00:55:15,437 --> 00:55:16,480
I'm on my way.

901
00:55:17,231 --> 00:55:18,398
I see.

902
00:55:19,024 --> 00:55:22,110
I came back to my room, but I can't sleep.

903
00:55:25,614 --> 00:55:26,782
I wanted to...

904
00:55:27,241 --> 00:55:29,409
see that movie too.

905
00:55:31,578 --> 00:55:32,746
Should we watch it together?

906
00:55:50,764 --> 00:55:51,765
I...

907
00:55:53,725 --> 00:55:55,686
prefer to watch movies alone.

908
00:56:02,693 --> 00:56:04,444
He wasn't interested after all.

909
00:56:04,653 --> 00:56:07,573
-I knew this would happen!
-Hey!

910
00:56:07,656 --> 00:56:09,700
You guys! What did I tell you?

911
00:56:09,783 --> 00:56:12,077
Take it back! Just take it back right now.

912
00:56:18,834 --> 00:56:19,835
Right?

913
00:56:21,003 --> 00:56:23,255
It's more comfortable
to watch movies alone.

914
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:26,925
I was about to go, but I'm lazy now

915
00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:29,261
and I might fall asleep.

916
00:56:30,345 --> 00:56:33,891
Well, enjoy the movie.
Let me know if it's good!

917
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:37,853
- Okay. See you tomorrow, Ms. Kim.
- Yes, see you tomorrow.

918
00:56:44,401 --> 00:56:45,485
Oh, how embarrassing.

919
00:56:58,165 --> 00:57:00,834
You said he was interested...

920
00:57:00,918 --> 00:57:03,253
I was a bit hasty, I admit.

921
00:57:03,587 --> 00:57:05,505
So much for your experience.

922
00:57:05,923 --> 00:57:07,633
You just keep getting it wrong.

923
00:57:12,387 --> 00:57:14,014
I'm a mess.

924
00:57:27,361 --> 00:57:29,363
How do you start dating again?

925
00:57:30,948 --> 00:57:33,450
It's been so long,
you've lost your touch, Kim Yu-mi.

926
00:57:42,626 --> 00:57:43,669
Oh, what now?

927
00:57:43,752 --> 00:57:47,047
WRITER KIM JU-HO

928
00:58:13,323 --> 00:58:15,409
NUMBER OF TICKETS

929
00:58:19,788 --> 00:58:21,498
WRITER KIM JU-HO

930
00:58:28,547 --> 00:58:30,757
- Yes, Mr. Kim.
- Hey, Shin PD.

931
00:58:31,299 --> 00:58:32,843
I heard you left with Ms. Kim.

932
00:58:33,719 --> 00:58:34,761
Well...

933
00:58:35,762 --> 00:58:38,890
- Yes, since it's late.
- I see.

934
00:58:39,433 --> 00:58:41,768
She's probably not asleep yet, right?

935
00:58:42,394 --> 00:58:43,979
But she's not answering her phone.

936
00:58:44,646 --> 00:58:48,692
Bring Ms. Kim and come over here.

937
00:58:50,110 --> 00:58:53,113
- Sorry?
- We're moving to a better spot.

938
00:58:53,280 --> 00:58:55,240
You know the food stall
by the beach, right?

939
00:58:55,532 --> 00:58:59,202
So bring Ms. Kim and hurry over.

940
00:59:00,829 --> 00:59:02,873
Seems like Ms. Kim
can't drink much, though.

941
00:59:03,123 --> 00:59:06,585
It's not about the drinking, okay?

942
00:59:07,627 --> 00:59:11,423
Anyway, both of you come. Okay?

943
00:59:11,506 --> 00:59:13,842
I'll text you the address.

944
00:59:17,888 --> 00:59:18,972
Come together.

945
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:20,474
You must.

946
00:59:21,933 --> 00:59:23,185
Ms. Kim can't make it.

947
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:26,563
Why?

948
00:59:26,646 --> 00:59:29,274
She went to the theater to watch a movie.

949
00:59:30,358 --> 00:59:32,694
It started. It's two hours long.

950
00:59:33,195 --> 00:59:34,196
What?

951
00:59:34,654 --> 00:59:37,199
- What movie?
- So don't call Ms. Kim.

952
00:59:38,075 --> 00:59:39,117
She won't pick up.

953
00:59:42,329 --> 00:59:43,330
Okay.

954
00:59:43,872 --> 00:59:44,873
Yes, I understand.

955
00:59:57,469 --> 00:59:59,179
NUMBER OF TICKETS

956
00:59:59,262 --> 01:00:00,430
I wanted to...

957
01:00:01,014 --> 01:00:03,475
see that movie too.

958
01:00:05,352 --> 01:00:06,603
Should we watch it together?

959
01:00:18,198 --> 01:00:19,491
I said I'm not going.

960
01:00:20,659 --> 01:00:23,328
Just enjoy yourselves.

961
01:00:25,914 --> 01:00:26,915
Ms. Kim.

962
01:00:27,541 --> 01:00:28,750
You're not asleep yet, are you?

963
01:00:33,964 --> 01:00:34,965
No.

964
01:00:36,174 --> 01:00:37,175
Why?

965
01:00:51,815 --> 01:00:52,816
Do you want to

966
01:00:53,108 --> 01:00:54,359
watch the movie together?

967
01:01:00,615 --> 01:01:02,284
He's showing interest, right?

968
01:01:03,368 --> 01:01:04,536
He's not interested.

969
01:01:22,345 --> 01:01:24,639
You said it's more comfortable
to watch movies alone.

970
01:01:36,276 --> 01:01:38,195
DO YOU WANT TO WATCH A MOVIE TOGETHER?

971
01:01:38,278 --> 01:01:40,697
YOU SAID IT'S MORE COMFORTABLE
TO WATCH MOVIES ALONE

972
01:01:54,628 --> 01:01:56,463
Do you want to watch the movie together?

973
01:02:33,541 --> 01:02:36,169
YUMI'S CELLS 3

974
01:02:36,544 --> 01:02:37,671
It's still in the early stages.

975
01:02:37,754 --> 01:02:39,422
But if it keeps growing

976
01:02:39,506 --> 01:02:40,507
it becomes love.

977
01:02:40,799 --> 01:02:42,884
Look at that, behind you!

978
01:02:43,385 --> 01:02:44,552
Do you like me?

979
01:02:44,928 --> 01:02:46,221
I want to date you.

980
01:02:46,429 --> 01:02:47,430
I'm sad.

981
01:02:47,764 --> 01:02:50,976
I haven't felt this fluttered
by Soon-rok in a long time.

982
01:02:51,101 --> 01:02:53,812
This is so unlike Soon-rok.

983
01:02:53,895 --> 01:02:55,981
Why are you interfering?

984
01:02:56,231 --> 01:02:58,566
Ms. Kim, you're so cool.

985
01:02:59,276 --> 01:03:00,610
If Shin Soon-rok feels the same

986
01:03:00,944 --> 01:03:02,696
that's when the relationship starts.

